{
    "name": "Lifeleecher",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Much like some of their orc kin, lifeleecher mortics often cover themselves in ritual scarring, brands, and auspicious tattoos. However, a lifeleecher mortic\u2019s skin is an ashen gray color, signaling their flirtation with death. Of all their markings, lifeleecher mortics most celebrate their death scar: the site of a mortal wound that would have felled creatures far more resilient than an orc, yet that failed to slay the lifeleecher mortic, instead unleashing their mortic heritage.<br/><br/> Lifeleecher mortics are roughly 6 feet tall and weigh about 230 pounds."
        }
    ],
